  "content": {
    "visible_text": "Studio Space Our dojo is available to rent as a studio space for weekly or monthly classes, one-off workshops, or series. The large open space filled with natural light and the clear-span training floor is ideal for movement arts, dance, gymnastics, Pilates, acrobatics, contact improv, partner work, martial arts, meditation, Tai Chi, Qi Gong, private yoga sessions, team building workshops, seminars, and even ambient music, performance, and reading events. The studio is located on the third floor of 2390 Mission Street #305 , with an after-hours entrance on the 20th Street side of the building. If you find the side entrance closed when attending an evening class, please use the call box to scroll, find, and dial “Quantum,” and the instructor will buzz you in. Please contact info@quantumsf.org for more information on rates and availability. Accessibility: Our Dojo is wheelchair accessible. No steps are required to enter the building, and our third-floor Dojo is accessible by elevator as well as stairs. We keep our space pristine and have wonderful ventilation, but occasionally use incense and mildly scented cleaning products, and occasionally have a short-haired dog onsite. We ask our students to abstain from using scented products while training at the Dojo. We offer wide benches for seating, as well as access to two all-gender restrooms on our floor. Our classes are primarily English-speaking, but have a diverse community available for translation support, as well as some Spanish-written resources. If you have any further questions or requests regarding accessibility, please don’t hesitate to reach out by  calling (415) 810-1420 or emailing rachael@quantumsf.org . Reviews Facebook Community Dojo Quantum Martial Arts is a registered 501(c)(3) nonprofit in the State of California, and we thrive on the generosity of people like you. All donations are tax-deductible. Quantum’s tax ID number is 26-1534597. No donation is too small, or too large. Whether it’s $20 or $20,000, every cent will be hugely appreciated and put to good use. Support Our Kids Donate now to support our youth scholarship program which allows families in need to train at reduced cost. We believe investment in our community involves investing in our youth. Our Sister Schools Our Seattle Dojo has served thousands of students since opening on Capitol Hill in 1995, and currently offers youth and adult classes in the Central District. Our Portland Dojo was established in 2020, and currently offers youth and adult classes in Southeast Portland. A WordPress.com Website .",
